SELF-AWARENESS.Definition: good knowledge and judgment about yourself

ILLUSION.Definition: idea or belief that is not true

REVOLUTIONARY.Definition: completely new and having a great effect

ONE SIZE FITS ALL.Definition: approach that is standard and not tailored to individual needs

VICE VERSA.Definition: in reverse order from the way something has been stated; the other way around

BULLSHIT.Definition: complete nonsense or something that is not true

HACKS.Definition: clever tip or technique for accomplishing something

FICTION.Definition: the type of book or story that is written about imaginary characters and events and not based on real people and facts

NON-FICTION.Definition: writing that is about real events and facts

PICK UP.Definition: to learn interesting or useful information from something

TERMINOLOGY.Definition: special words or expressions used in relation to a particular subject or activity

CULTURE.Definition: the way of life, especially the general customs and beliefs, of a particular group of people at a particular time

INTERMEDIATE.Definition: having reached a fairly good level of skill or knowledge

VOCABULARY.Definition: all the words known and used by a particular person

CLOSING A LOT OF DOORS.Definition: not giving any chance for a lot of things

COMFORT ZONE.Definition: a situation in which you feel comfortable and in which your ability and determination are not being tested

BORED.Definition: tired and unhappy because something is not interesting or because you have nothing to do

DEDICATED.Definition: believing that something is very important and giving a lot of time and energy to it

RANDOM.Definition: happening, done, or chosen by chance rather than according to a plan

COMMITTED.Definition: loyal and willing to give your time and energy to something that you believe in

STRATEGY.Definition: a detailed plan for achieving success

TRASH.Definition: something that is of low quality

BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.Definition: and so on; and so forth

THRIVE.Definition: to grow, develop, or be successful

DOUBT.Definition: (a feeling of) not being certain about something
